data.description: Rare find in Brittany's Garden! This wonderful 3 bedroom, 2 and a half bath home with a 36' x 24' workshop, situated on a cul-de-sac lot is minutes away from the ever expanding Trail Creek Village shopping center and a short drive to UGA/Downtown Athens. This peaceful neighborhood feels worlds away but offers great convenience to shopping, dining and much more. On the main level of the home is the cozy living room, complete with a fireplace, invites you to unwind after a long day. The kitchen is equipped with stainless steel appliances, granite countertops, and ample cabinetry for storage and a pantry. The kitchen seamlessly flows into the dining area with french doors leading to the back deck, creating a perfect space for entertaining family and friends. Just before the attached 2 car garage is the laundry room to your left and a large closet to your right for additional storage. The home features three spacious bedrooms, each offering a retreat for relaxation. The primary suite is on the main level, featuring tile shower and garden soaking tub. The additional bedrooms upstairs share full hall bathroom, ensuring both convenience and comfort for everyone in the household. The right hand side bedroom features a large bonus/rec room ideal for a home office area or more room for hobbies or a crafting area. One of the standout features of this property is the expansive fenced yard. The private outdoor space provides the perfect backdrop for al fresco dining, gardening, or play. Whether you're enjoying a cup of coffee on the back deck or hosting a barbecue while enjoying the above ground pool, the possibilities for outdoor enjoyment are endless. For those who love to tinker or need a space for hobbies, the large secondary garage doubles as a workshop area. With plenty of room for tools, equipment or another vehicle, this versatile space is ideal for DIY projects or storing outdoor gear. This garage/workshop features its own electric panel, 2 roll up garage doors, and measures 36' long by 24' wide per public record. Above the workshop is a completely floored attic area (864 sq. ft. per public record) offering an ample amount of additional storage. Imagine living in a quiet cul-de-sac, enjoying the privacy of a fenced yard, and having a dedicated workshop for your hobbies. Don't miss the opportunity to make this updated and well maintained home yours!
